tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE Patients (
  patient_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  patient_name VARCHAR(50),
  patient_age INT,
  patient_gender CHAR(1),
  diagnosis VARCHAR(100),
  treatment VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE patients (
    patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    address TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE researchers (
    researcher_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50),
    institution VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE datasets (
    dataset_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_name VARCHAR(100),
    dataset_size INT,
    researcher_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (researcher_id) REFERENCES researchers(researcher_id)
)

CREATE TABLE patient_information (
    patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    patient_name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    dataset_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (dataset_id) REFERENCES datasets(dataset_id)
)

CREATE TABLE healthcare_outcomes (
    outcome_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    outcome_name VARCHAR(50),
    outcome_description TEXT,
    patient_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient_information(patient_id)
)

CREATE TABLE patients (
    patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    patient_name VARCHAR(50),
    patient_age INT,
    patient_gender VARCHAR(10),
    diagnosis VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE patient_doctor (
    patient_id INT,
    doctor_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (patient_id, doctor_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patients(patient_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (doctor_id) REFERENCES doctors(doctor_id)
);

CREATE TABLE patient_treatment (
    patient_id INT,
    treatment_id INT,
    treatment_date DATE,
    PRIMARY KEY (patient_id, treatment_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patients(patient_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (treatment_id) REFERENCES treatments(treatment_id)
);
